what_i_learned: |
  Today we continued preparing for our final symposium by focusing on improving
  and modifying our presentation slides. We reviewed our current slides as a
  team and made adjustments to improve the organization, clarity, and overall
  flow of our presentation. We worked on making sure that the important parts
  of our research were explained effectively and that the audience would be
  able to understand our project.

  During our session, our mentor helped us by reviewing the technical aspects
  of our project and explaining different codes, methods, and terminologies
  again. This discussion helped us strengthen our understanding of the concepts
  behind our work and gave us more confidence in explaining our methodology,
  models, and results during the presentation. We also discussed how to simplify
  complex research terms so that they could be communicated clearly to a wider
  audience.

  After making the slide improvements, we conducted a mock presentation among
  ourselves. Each team member practiced their assigned section, and we provided
  feedback on presentation style, timing, and areas that could be improved. This
  practice helped us identify small issues and improve the transitions between
  different sections of the presentation.

  Overall, today's session was very helpful in preparing us for the symposium.
  It improved our confidence, strengthened our teamwork, and allowed us to make
  the final improvements needed to present our research professionally.

